            <p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height:12.0pt"><b>
            <span lang="EN-US" style="color: #570E0A">
            <font size="2" face="Arial">The Cider,</font></span></b></p>
            <p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height:12.0pt">
            <span lang="EN-US" style="color: #570E0A"><b>
            <font size="2" face="Arial">&nbsp;</font></b><font size="2" face="Arial">The 
            annual cider production is estimated at approximately 110 millions 
            of liters per year which are mainly destined to internal consumption 
            internal consumption. For its production, 14% of the apple with in 
            the industry is used. The national consumption is approximately of 
            2,7 liters / hab / year, having registered a 17% fall within the 
            last four years, despite the progressive price decrease.&nbsp;</font></span></p>
            <p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height:12.0pt">
            <span lang="EN-US" style="color: #570E0A">
            <font size="2" face="Arial">50% of the apple production is destined 
            to the industry. Around 15% of the industrialized fruit is used to 
            produce cider. The cider production is at approximately 110 millions 
            of liters.&nbsp;</font></span></p>
            <p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height:12.0pt">
            <span lang="EN-US" style="color: #570E0A">
            <font size="2" face="Arial">The 12% drop within the last three-year 
            period was a consequence of the decrease in the consumption and the 
            noticeable increase of the raw material value. The price of the 
            apple has tripled regarding its historic average during this period.</font></span></p>
            <p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height:12.0pt">
            <span lang="EN-US" style="color: #570E0A">
            <font size="2" face="Arial">The production value is of 85 millions 
            of dollars, including 9 million in exportations.</font></span></p>
            <p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height:12.0pt"><b>
            <span lang="EN-US" style="color: #570E0A">
            <font size="2" face="Arial">&nbsp;</font></span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Arial; color: #570E0A"><font size="2">THE 
            CONSUMPTION</font></span></b></p>
            <p style="margin-top:5.25pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.5pt;margin-left:
10.5pt;line-height:12.0pt">
            <span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Arial; color: #570E0A">
            <font size="2">The national consumption is of approximately 2,7 
            liters/ hab/ year, presenting a 17% reduction in the last four years 
            despite the progressive price increase.</font></span></p>
            <p style="line-height:12.0pt">
            <span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Arial; color: #570E0A">
            <font size="2">&nbsp; &nbsp; On the other hand, during this period, a quality 
            decrease of the product has impacted negatively on sales. </font>
            </span></p>
            <p style="margin-top:5.25pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.5pt;margin-left:
10.5pt;line-height:12.0pt">
            <span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Arial; color: #570E0A">
            <font size="2">The government department of the industry made an 
            investigation of the processing plants forbidding those which did 
            not use raw material authorized by the Argentine Food Code. </font>
            </span></p>
            <p style="margin-top:5.25pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.5pt;margin-left:
10.5pt;line-height:12.0pt"><b>
            <span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Arial; color: #570E0A">
            <font size="2">THE EXPORTATIONS</font></span></b></p>
            <p style="margin-top:5.25pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.5pt;margin-left:
10.5pt;line-height:12.0pt">
            <span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Arial; color: #570E0A">
            <font size="2">The annual sales abroad sum up a total of 7 million 
            liters, hardly 7% of the production.</font></span></p>
            <p style="margin-top:5.25pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.5pt;margin-left:
10.5pt;line-height:12.0pt">
            <span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Arial; color: #570E0A">
            <font size="2">And the FOB price per liter fell 14%, with an average 
            value of U$S 0,8.</font></span></p>
            <p style="line-height:12.0pt">
            <span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Arial; color: #570E0A">
            <font size="2">&nbsp; &nbsp; The shipping reached its largest volumes between 
            the months of October and December.</font></span></p>
            <p style="margin-top:5.25pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.5pt;margin-left:
10.5pt;line-height:12.0pt">
            <span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Arial; color: #570E0A">
            <font size="2">The main destination of our exports is the Mercosur. 
            Argentina cannot compete with other countries which export to the 
            Northern hemisphere  as is Spain  due to the shipping costs.</font></span></p>
            <p style="margin-top:5.25pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.5pt;margin-left:
10.5pt;line-height:12.0pt" align="center">
            <img border="0" src="../images/logo_2.jpg"></p>
            <p style="margin-top:5.25pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.5pt;margin-left:
10.5pt;line-height:12.0pt"><b>
            <span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Arial; color: #570E0A">
            <font size="2">THE IMPORTATIONS</font></span></b></p>
            <p style="margin-top:5.25pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.5pt;margin-left:
10.5pt;line-height:12.0pt">
            <span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Arial; color: #570E0A">
            <font size="2">The imported cider volumes are insignificant and with 
            a decreasing tendency.</font></span></p>
            <p style="margin-top:5.25pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.5pt;margin-left:
10.5pt;line-height:12.0pt">
            <span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Arial; color: #570E0A">
            <font size="2">An atypical year was 1995, in which volumes that did 
            not coincide with the tendency were imported. It was due to an 
            increase in the imports of Spanish cider, as a consequence of the 
            high prices of the national ciders.</font></span></p>
            <p style="margin-top:5.25pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.5pt;margin-left:
10.5pt;line-height:12.0pt">
            <span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Arial; color: #570E0A">
            <font size="2">In 1997, 200 thousand liters were hardly reached, 
            which represent 0,5% of the production.</font></span></p>
            <p style="margin-top:5.25pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.5pt;margin-left:
10.5pt;line-height:12.0pt">
            <span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Arial; color: #570E0A">
            <font size="2">&nbsp; &nbsp;Since 1993, the CIF price per liter grew a 24%, 
            reaching a value of U$S 1,24 /liter in 1997. Most of the ciders that 
            are imported are Spanish. The main part of the industry buys the raw 
            material to third-parties. Only 10% of the companies are their own 
            fruit producers.</font></span></p>
            <p style="margin-top:5.25pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.5pt;margin-left:
10.5pt;line-height:12.0pt">
            <span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Arial; color: #570E0A">
            <font size="2">Half of the companies produce the base broth at their 
            plants, and buy 25 % to third-parties and the rest they combine with 
            both modalities.</font></span></p>
            <p style="margin-top:5.25pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.5pt;margin-left:
10.5pt;line-height:12.0pt">
            <span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Arial; color: #570E0A">
            <font size="2">&nbsp; &nbsp; Most of the companies have their fractioning 
            plant in the Federal Capital o in Buenos Aires. The proximity of the 
            main consumption centers reduces the freight costs.</font></span></p>
            <p style="margin-top:5.25pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.5pt;margin-left:
10.5pt;line-height:12.0pt">
            <span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Arial; color: #570E0A">
            <font size="2">During the last years, new technology was 
            incorporated to the Bottling line, with machinery that comes from 
            the renovation in the soft-drink Bottling sector. The only machinery 
            specific to the cider production sector is the bottle capping 
            machine which place the tinplate and wire muselete. </font></span>
            </p>
            <p style="margin-top:5.25pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.5pt;margin-left:
10.5pt;line-height:12.0pt">
            <span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Arial; color: #570E0A">
            <font size="2">The facilities of the industrial sector allow a 
            production of 550 millions of liters, with an important inactive 
            period, given the products low consumption and the difficulty to 
            access other markets.</font></span></p>
            <p style="margin-top:5.25pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.5pt;margin-left:
10.5pt;line-height:12.0pt">
            <span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Arial; color: #570E0A">
            <font size="2">80% is produced between the months of February and 
            June, period in which the broth base or apple juice is prepared. 
            Once the broth has fermented, it is fractioned mainly into 910 cc.</font></span></p>
            <p style="margin-top:5.25pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.5pt;margin-left:
10.5pt;line-height:12.0pt">
            <span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Arial; color: #570E0A">
            <font size="2">The sector occupies around 800 personnel during the 
            whole year and 400 temporary personnel. </font></span></p>
            <p style="margin-top:5.25pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.5pt;margin-left:
10.5pt;line-height:12.0pt"><b>
            <span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Arial; color: #570E0A">
            <font size="2">INDUSTRIALIZATION</font></span></b></p>
            <p style="margin-top:5.25pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.5pt;margin-left:
10.5pt;line-height:12.0pt">
            <span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Arial; color: #570E0A">
            <font size="2">The generic denomination of <b>cider</b> or <b>
            genuine cider</b> refers to the drink that is obtained by the normal 
            fermentation of apple juice, with or without the addition of pear 
            juice, in a proportion no higher than 10%. The finished product can 
            or cannot be gasified with CO2.</font></span></p>
            <p style="margin-top:5.25pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.5pt;margin-left:
10.5pt;line-height:12.0pt">
            <span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Arial; color: #570E0A">
            <font size="2">The general conditions for the production 
            establishments are specified in the Second Chapter of the Argentina 
            Food Code (Law 18284/69, Decree 2126/71).</font></span></p>
            <p style="margin-top:5.25pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.5pt;margin-left:
10.5pt;line-height:12.0pt">
            <span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Arial; color: #570E0A">
            <font size="2">The terms, requirements and characteristics for the 
            cider are specified in the XIII Chapter of the same Code.</font></span></p>
            <p style="line-height:12.0pt">
            <span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Arial; color: #570E0A">
            <font size="2">&nbsp; &nbsp; The ciders that are commercialized within the 
            local market must contain a minimum 4% of alcohol in volume, except 
            the non-alcoholic ciders which can only contain 0,5% of alcohol as a 
            maximum.</font></span></p>
            <p style="line-height:12.0pt">
            <span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Arial; color: #570E0A">
            <font size="2">&nbsp;Cortesia Cider is the only production plant in 
            Mendoza that plants and harvests its own apples. As also, processes, 
            produces and bottles all of its products in the same production 
            plant.</font></span></p>
